<H3> <TI>   Gonzalez, Israel's Rabin Hold Talks in Madrid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2102162094 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 1500 GMT 
21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2102162094 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin is in Spain on 
a two-day official visit. In his first meeting with Prime 
Minister Gonzalez at the Moncloa, only questions relating to the 
Middle East peace process were discussed. Present at the 
meeting were Foreign Minister Javier Solana and the ambassadors 
of the two countries. Solana stressed that Spain will try to 
play an active role in achieving peace between Arabs and 
Israelis. Rabin will be meeting a delegation of Spanish 
businessmen this afternoon. 

