<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Reports Turkish Violations of Airspace </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2002175294 Athens ATHENS NEWS in English 20 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC2002175294 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ATHENS NEWS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Turkey has turned up the heat in the Aegean, 
stepping up activities through repeated violations of Greek 
national air space, defense ministry sources said yesterday. 
  Turkish warplanes are regularly intercepted by Greek 
fighters 
in Greek national air space, but the sources said Turkish 
sorties over the Aegean were now being flown in attack 
formations and planes armed with air-to-air and air-to-surface 
missiles had buzzed Greek navy boats patrolling Greek waters. 
They added that two Turkish naval vessels had also strayed into 
Greek waters off the island of Milos, 77 nautical miles from 
Pireaivs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

