<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Rejects Czech Bosnia Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2102144194 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1200 
GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2102144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Ankara today, Turkish Defense Minister Mehmet 
Golhan rejected in principle the personal initiative of his 
Czech counterpart Antonin Baudys for resolving the Bosnian 
situation. During his talks with Antonin Baudys, Golhan stated 
that the initiative did not reflect the present situation in 
Bosnia- Herzegovina. The Turkish side opposed above all the 
supposition that the conflict in this former Yugoslav republic 
was religiously motivated. According to the Turkish minister of 
defense, Ankara was aiming above all to preserve the territorial 
integrity of Bosnia-Herzegovina as a state that had been 
recognized by the United Nations and by the international 
community. The Baudys initiative is, on the contrary, alleged 
to envisage the split of the republic. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

