<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cetin, CSCE Official Discuss Nagorno-Karabakh </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1802162894 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1545 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1802162894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Feb 18 (AA) -- The head of the Minsk Group, 
in the frame of the Conference on Security and Cooperation in 
Europe (CSCE), Sweden's representative Jan Elliasson, visited 
Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin on Friday [18 February]. 
  Elliasson, who supported a peaceful solution on the 
Nagorno-Karabakh problem, took over the term chairmanship from 
Italy. 
  Eliasson, before meeting with Cetin, said he came to Turkey 
to exchange opinions with the concerned sides adding he will 
later go to the region and meet with other sides. 
  He said defending the international community's and CSCE's 
principles were very important and added that the 
Nagorno-Karabakh problem should be solved in political ways. 
  Foreign Minister Cetin said most of the Azeri territory were 
under Armenian occupation. `It is very diffucult to hold a peace 
conference before this occupying attitude ends,' he added. 
  Cetin said Nagorno-Karabakh was Azeri territory and with the 
CSCE resolutions this was once again confirmed. 
  Recalling that Turkey wanted Armenians to withdraw from the 
Azeri territory soon the foreign minister said Turkey was ready 
to do its best on the issue. 
  Eliasson will leave for Baku, where he will hold a series of 
contacts with Azeri officials. 
  Turkey and Russia are active partners in the nine-nation 
Minsk Group that is working to arrange an Armenian withdrawal 
before an international conference can convene on the future of 
the enclave. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-39784 </DOCNO>
