<H3> <TI>   Government Protests Greek Border Action </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1802183294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1802183294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] Turkey has protested Greece refusing entry into the 
country of two religious officials who were sent by Turkey to 
provide religious services for the Turkish minority in western 
Thrace. 
  A Foreign Ministry statement on the subject noted that two 
religious officials who left for western Thrace yesterday, were 
sent back by Greek authorities at the Ipsala border checkpoint. 
The statement added that the Greek ambassador to Ankara was 
summoned to the Foreign Ministry and a protest was lodged with 
Greece in connection with the incident. 
  The statement said: There is a lesson to be learned with 
regard to contemporary concepts and norms from the fact that 
Greece -- a member of the European Union -- is unable to 
tolerate an invitation to two religious officials from abroad 
extended by a minority in the country in order to meet their 
needs for worship during a holy month. 

</TEXT>

