<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Explosion at Democracy Party Headquarters Kills 1 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1802194794 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1800 
GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1802194794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] An explosion occurred at the Democracy Party 
headquarters on Ankara's Necati Bey Street this evening. 
According to initial reports, one person was killed and 11 were 
injured in the incident. Two of the injured are reported to be 
in serious condition. The explosion, which occurred at 1815 on 
the fifth floor of the headquarters building, damaged the 
building and shattered the windows of other buildings in the 
area. 
  Ankara Governor Erdogan Sahinoglu toured the area. He said 
one person was killed and 11 others were injured in the 
explosion. Pointing out that work is under way to identify the 
victims, Sahinoglu said it is believed that a bomb placed in the 
elevator shaft of the building caused the explosion. 
  It was learned that the name of the dead person is Ekrem 
Akcakaya, who is not connected with the party, according to 
witnesses. 

</TEXT>

