<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Criticizes Bombing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1902160294 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1500 GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1902160294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Feb 19 (A.A) -- President Suleyman Demirel 
on Saturday [19 February] condemned Friday's bomb attack on 
Democracy Party (DEP) headquarters which killed one and wounded 
sixteen people. 
  "Our country needs peace and quiet. I am calling on everyone 
to stand against the shedding of blood for any reason," Demirel 
said in his message. 
  He also sent a message to DEP party leader in which he 
expressed sorrow over the attack and condemned the incident. 
  A bomb that exploded in the headquarters of the Democracy 
Party (DEP) early in the evening on Friday killed one and 
wounded another sixteen people. 
  The attack was later claimed by the Islamic Jihad 
organization. 

</TEXT>

