<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   ANAP Adalar Mayor Killed in Istanbul </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1902165994 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1600 
GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1902165994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] Recep Koc, ANAP [Motherland Party] mayor of Adalar, 
has been killed in an armed attack. According to information 
obtained by a TRT correspondent, Koc and a citizen named Osman 
Ozen had an argument at the Buyukada marketplace. Ozen pulled 
his gun and fired twice at Koc. Koc, who was wounded in his 
stomach and leg, was taken to the Kartal State Hospital, where 
he died during surgery. 
  Eyewitnesses reported that Mehmet Ozkorkmaz and Zekariya 
Orali, who were accompanying Koc, were also wounded following 
the armed attack by Ozen. The assailant Ozen was later taken 
into custody. Officials from the Kartal State Hospital stated 
that Koc died as a result of heavy loss of blood. The wounded 
are in good condition. 
  ANAP leader Mesut Yilmaz, who was in Istanbul at the time of 
the incident, expressed his sorrow over the loss of the mayor of 
Adalar. 

</TEXT>

