<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Juppe Welcomes Russia's Inclusion in UNPROFOR </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1802180294 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1700 
GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1802180294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Two days before the expiration of the NATO 
ultimatum, the Bosnian Serbs are making more appeasing 
statements. [passage omitted] 
  We know that Russia played an important role in the 
diplomatic breakthrough of the last 24 hours. The Moscow 
mediation has offered the Serbs an honorable face-saving device. 
Alain Juppe has welcomed the prospect of sending Russian 
peace-keeping forces to Sarajevo. Interviewed by Harry Sago, the 
French foreign minister explained that he was asking for such a 
measure: 
  [Begin Juppe recording] For nearly 10 months I have been 
asking the Russians to join us in the field. It is not about 
asking the Russian soldiers to be [word indistinct] buffer. It 
is about putting contingents from as many countries as possible 
under the UN banner, under UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] 
command -- which is led as you know by a French general for the 
whole of the former Yugoslavia, by a British general for Bosnia, 
and by another French general, General Soubirou for Sarajevo. I 
will be pleased if a Russian peace-keeping contingent is 
included. We are told it [latest diplomatic breakthrough] is a 
Russian victory, I say it is a European victory. We have never 
ceased to ask for it. I am happy from the bottom of my heart 
because this could be an element that would facilitate the 
settlement of the problem. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

