<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pakistan Urges UNHRC Fact-Finding Mission </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2302075294 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 
GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2302075294 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan has said at the Geneva-based UN Human 
Rights Commission that the international human rights groups 
have condemned India for systematic and blatant human rights 
violations in occupied Kashmir. Pakistan's delegate Shafqat 
Kakakhel told the Commission that human rights groups and 
agencies have charged the Indian occupation forces with cold 
blooded murders, unjustified arrests, killing in custody, 
molestation of Kashmiri women, and acts of arson. In response 
to a statement by the Indian delegate, he said the Commission 
should send a fact-finding team to occupied Jammu and Kashmir to 
study the exact state of human rights violations there. He said 
this is the only way the international community can know and 
try to end atrocities being committed by the Indian forces in 
the Indian-held valley. 

</TEXT>

