<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   EU Observer Meets With Mikhailidhis, Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2302105394 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1000 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2302105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Serge Abou, the European Union [EU] observer on the 
Cyprus issue, said that the signing of an agreement between the 
two communities on the confidence-building measures [CBM's] 
would be a significant achievement. Mr. Abou also noted that 
such an agreement would create the correct impetus, as he put 
it, toward achieving an overall Cyprus solution. 
  In a statement after his meeting with Foreign Minister 
Alekos 
Mikhailidhis this morning, Mr. Abou described the contacts he 
had with President Glavkos Kliridhis and Gustave Feissel, the UN 
secretary general's alternate special representative in Cyprus, 
as very important in view of the report on the Cyprus issue he 
will prepare for the EU's Council of Ministers. 
  Responding to a question on the CBM's compatibility with EU 
norms, Mr. Abou said that the United Nations has assured him 
that there is no problem. Nevertheless, he added there is no 
easy answer to this issue. Answering another question on 
Turkey's stance, he noted that during his recent visit to that 
country he received assurances that Turkey desires a Cyprus 
solution. 

</TEXT>

