<F P=100> SWITZERLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Citizens Vote For Transit Traffic Ban </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2002213394 Vienna ORF Teletext in German 1852 GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2002213394 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna ORF Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In the Swiss referendum on a transit ban for 
trucks, the majority of the Swiss and the required majority of 
cantons came out in favor of such a ban. Thirteen full and six 
half cantons accepted the referendum, which corresponds to 16 
"canton votes" and, thus, a clear "yes" to the ban. A total of 
52 percent of the Swiss voted for the referendum. 
  Up until now, Switzerland has had a 28-tonne limit for 
trucks 
and a ban on night driving. The transit traffic ban says that 
as of 2004, goods may be transported through Switzerland only by 
train and that no new roads through the Alps may be built. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

