<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Garcia Vargas Favors Safe Area Extension </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202183894 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 1400 GMT 22 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2202183894 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Spanish Defense Minister Julian Garcia Vargas is in 
favor of the Bosnian city of Mostar, which is entrusted to the 
Spanish blue helmets, being included by the United Nations in 
the first group of safe areas to receive the same kind of 
treatment as that applied to Sarajevo. 
  In statements made after meeting the Israeli Prime Minister 
Yitzaq Rabin, Garcia Vargas admitted that UN Secretary General 
Butrus-Ghali seemed to have given priority to the cities of 
Tuzla and Srebrenica. However, according to the Spanish defense 
minister, the momentum could also take in Mostar. 
  As for the presence of the Spanish blue helmets in Bosnia, 
Garcia Vargas pointed out that their presence depends on what 
happens in the conflict as a whole. The minister added that in 
this situation Spain would not act on its own, and it would 
fulfill its obligations -- i.e. in the short-term it would 
continue its work as part of the UN forces in Bosnia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

