<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government `Would Not Increase' Troops in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2102220394 Madrid Teletexto TVE in Spanish 1915 GMT 21 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2102220394 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid Teletexto TVE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to [Spanish Defense Minister Julian] 
Garcia Vargas, the Spanish soldiers deployed in Sarajevo will 
not intervene even if NATO were to bomb the Serbs, because: We 
do not belong to the air task force. 
  Spain answered NATO by saying that it would not increase the 
number of blue helmets in Bosnia; however it can send more 
observers, between five and 10 officers. The Spaniards will 
stay in the Herzegovina area. 
  For his part, PSOE [Spanish Socialist Workers Party] 
spokesperson Solana [Spanish foreign minister], said that the 
NATO ultimatum had been successful. Now let us think about the 
next step. 

</TEXT>

