<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Denmark </F>
<H3> <TI>   * SDP on European Parliament Election Strategy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20380A Copenhagen BERLINGSKE TIDENDE SONDAG in Danish 6 
Feb 94 p 4 </F>

<F P=103> 94P20380A </F>
<F P=104>  Copenhagen BERLINGSKE TIDENDE SONDAG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Danish </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by Louse Fleischer: "Liberal Party To Be the Main </F>
Enemy"] 
  [Text] The Social Democratic Party [SDP] during the 
election campaign leading up to the European Parliament election 
will define itself by hitting the Liberals. The Liberal Party 
will be the main enemy in the campaign leading up to the 
election set for 9 June. 
  The leading candidate for the SDP, Kirsten Jensen, 
acknowledged following a news conference at Christiansborg 
yesterday that it is the open strategy of the party to hit the 
Liberals as much as possible during the campaign. "We will try 
to confront the Liberals during the entire campaign. Because 
they are most visible. We want to meet with Liberal figures and 
debate with them at every opportunity we can arrange," said 
Jensen. 
  During the election the SDP wants to sell itself under the 
slogan "A human Europe." 
  "We will demonstrate that it makes a difference whether one 
votes nonsocialist or SDP. Social democracy stands for defending 
the national compromise [Edinburgh opt-out package]," said 
Jensen. 
  "Some people are trying to make this into a third referendum 
on Danish membership relations with the [European] Union, or a 
referendum on the Western European Union. But this is 
irrelevant," said the SDP member of the European Parliament. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

