<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Envoy Reiterates Support for Turkey </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2202125994 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1100 
GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2202125994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Russia has declared that it fully supports Turkey's 
territorial integrity and unity, and condemns the actions 
perpetrated by the PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan] terrorist 
organization. 
  According to a statement issued by Foreign Ministry Deputy 
Spokesman Ferhat Ataman, Russian Ambassador in Ankara Albert 
Sergeyevich Chernyshev was invited to the Foreign Ministry 
following the appearance of press items regarding a PKK meeting 
to be held in Moscow. 
  Foreign Ministry Under Secretary Ambassador Ozdem Sanberk 
received Chernyshev and inquired as to the truth of the items 
that appeared in the press. Replying that he will immediately 
ask Moscow to send information regarding this issue, Chernyshev 
stated that there was no question of a change in Russia's policy 
concerning Turkey. 
  Noting that Russia fully supports Turkey's territorial 
integrity and unity, Chernyshev stated that his country has 
absolutely no connections with the PKK terrorist organization, 
and added that they condemn the terrorism perpetrated by the PKK. 

</TEXT>

