<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbian Deputy Foreign Minister Arrives for Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2102160294 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1445 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2102160294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Feb 21 (AA) -- Serbian Deputy Foreign 
Minister Zivadin Jovanovic arrived in Ankara on Monday [21 
February] to hold talks on the recent developments in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  Jovanovic told at Ankara's Esenboga Airport that he will 
pave 
official contacts to increase the dialogues on the problem in 
Bosnia, adding he will also discuss peace and stability in the 
former Yugoslavia and the Balkans. [sentence as received] 
  Jovanovic recalled that the two country foreign ministers 
earlier met in New York. 
  Asked if his visit would contribute to the problem while 
Turkey's policy was supporting the Muslims, Jovanovic said 
`Turkey, being a Balkan and a European country, contributed a 
lot to the efforts.' 
  Jovanovic said Serbian foreign minister sent a message to 
Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin last week. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

