<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Serbian Deputy Foreign Minister Zivadin Jovanovic, 
who is currently on an official visit in Ankara, was received by 
Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin. Cetin conferred with the 
visiting deputy minister. 
  In reply to reporters' questions upon arrival at the Foreign 
Ministry, Cetin declared that the NATO ultimatum has attained 
its goal and the security of the 20-km radius area surrounding 
Sarajevo has been guaranteed. Answering another question, Cetin 
said that the Serbian siege around other towns in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina must also be lifted and Turkey is continuing 
its initiatives in various capitals and with NATO in this regard. 

</TEXT>

