<H3> <TI>   Council of Europe's Lalumiere Ends Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2302081894 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
2100 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2302081894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Catherine Lalumiere, secretary general of the 
Council of Europe, has said Turkey's stability is important for 
all the European countries. She expressed the belief that 
Turkey will overcome certain difficulties it is experiencing, 
adding that stability in Turkey means stability in Europe. 
  Lalumiere ended her contacts in Ankara and left Turkey this 
evening. In a statement to Turkish Radio and Television at 
Esenboga Airport, she said that while in Turkey she exchanged 
views on the problems of the countries in the region. I also 
had the opportunity to receive information on the [word 
indistinct] problems, she said. 

</TEXT>

