<H3> <TI>   `Full Agreement' Reached With Turkish Cypriots </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2202151394 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1100 
GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2202151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Rauf Denktas, president of the Turkish Republic of 
Northern Cyprus, who is currently on a working visit in Turkey, 
met and conferred with Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin. Cetin and 
Denktas declared that full agreement was reached during the 
talks between delegations, which ended last night. 
  Cetin also conveyed get well wishes to Denktas, who 
underwent 
ophthalmological examinations at Gulhane Military Hospital this 
morning. Denktas will call on Prime Minister Tansu Ciller this 
afternoon. Denktas and his delegation will leave Turkey 
tomorrow. 

