<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cindoruk Rejects European Demand To Observe Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1802151094 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1300 
GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1802151094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over still of Husamettin Cindoruk, </F>
speaker of the Turkish Grand National Assembly] 
  [Text] Husamettin Cindoruk, speaker of the Turkish Grand 
National Assembly, has declared that the European Parliament 
demand to set up a mission of foreign observers to follow the 
election campaign in a certain region in Turkey is unacceptable. 
  Cindoruk sent a letter to the president of the European 
Parliament following the Parliament's decision on the subject. 
In his letter, Cindoruk noted that the decision by the European 
Parliament blatantly discriminates against the various regions 
in Turkey and ignores the maturity of democratic processes. 
Cindoruk remarked that there is no logical reason whatsoever to 
rely on observers to secure a just and free election atmosphere 
during the upcoming local elections. 

</TEXT>

