<H3> <TI>   $725 Million Loan Secured From Japan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2102181294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2102181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Excerpt] Turkey has exported state bonds worth $725 
million to Japan. According to an agreement signed in Tokyo, of 
the total loan 45 billion yen will be paid back in eight years 
and with an interest rate of 5.45 percent. The remaining 30 
billion yen will be paid back in 10 years at an interest rate of 
5.75 percent. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

