GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2202193094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over still of President Suleyman </F>
Demirel] 
  [Text] President Suleyman Demirel has declared that 
Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] 
can use Turkish ports for its transportation needs, following 
the Greek decision to close the Salonika Port to Macedonia's 
use. Demirel had a telephone conversation with Macedonian 
President Kiro Gligorov today. 
  According to a statement issued by the President's Press 
Center, recent developments in the Balkans as well as 
Macedonia's transportation needs were discussed during the 
Demirel-Gligorov conversation. 

