<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trade Figures Note Increase in Exports to East </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1902204794 Vienna KURIER in German 19 Feb 94 p 17 </F>
<F P=103> AU1902204794 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna KURIER </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Export Success to East Europe"] </F>
  [Text] Austria's exports to East Europe in 1993 rose by 5 
percent to 59.3 billion schillings; the surplus now already 
amounts to 16.3 billion schillings. The most important partner 
is Hungary (7.9 billion schillings), which is the fifth largest 
buyer of Austrian goods in the world. Exports to The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia, Croatia, Albania, and Slovenia 
experienced a particularly strong upswing. 

</TEXT>

