<F P=102>  AU2302152294 Duesseldorf HANDELSBLATT in German 23 Feb 94 p 
12 </F>

<F P=103> AU2302152294 </F>
<F P=104>  Duesseldorf HANDELSBLATT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["vwd"-attributed report: "Bonn: Talks on Iranian Debts </F>
Continue"] 
  [Text] Bonn -- The Federal Government and the Iranian 
Government are interested in refinancing some 3 billion German 
marks [DM] in Iranian debts through credits covered by Hermes 
export guarantees. A spokeswoman for the Federal Economics 
Ministry stated on Tuesday [22 February] that, as far as Bonn is 
concerned, the point is to prevent financial damage, while Iran 
did not want to cut itself off from the possibility of being 
granted further Hermes guarantees. Both sides have differing 
views regarding, among other things, the beginning of the 
repayment of debts and the number of installments. Before the 
beginning of a new round of talks, the Iranian side will be 
contacted by telephone at the end of the week, the spokeswoman 
said. 

