<F P=100> PORTUGAL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Greets Israeli Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302101194 Lisbon Radio Renascenca in Portuguese to Europe 
0900 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2302101194 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon Radio Renascenca </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin arrived in 
Lisbon 30 minutes earlier than expected. He was welcomed at the 
airport by Portuguese Foreign Minister Durao Barroso. Rabin did 
not say much on arrival, but he did say that any statement on 
the withdrawal of Israeli soldiers from the Gaza Strip and 
Jericho can only be made after the meetings with the Portuguese 
authorities. Raquel Abecassis reports. 
  [Abecassis] The Israeli prime minister said he did not want 
to speak to journalists, but ended up agreeing to a news 
conference later after, his meetings with the Portuguese prime 
minister and foreign minister. 
  [Begin Rabin recording, in English] First, I am in Portugal 
as a guest of the prime minister. I am just now beginning my 
visit. I believe it will be better to discuss questions 
relating to the peace negotiations first with the prime minister 
and government officials; only then will I make a public 
statement. Thank you. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

