<H3> <TI>   Deputy Parliament Speaker Resigns </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1902183594 Lisbon Radio Renascenca in Portuguese to Europe 
1800 GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1902183594 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon Radio Renascenca </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Leonor Beleza could not resist the political and 
personal pressure that has now led her to hand in her 
resignation as deputy speaker of parliament and member of 
parliament. Prime Minister Cavaco Silva and Parliament Speaker 
Barbosa de Melo have already received the resignation. Beleza 
argues that, despite proof that she has no civil or criminal 
responsibility for irregularities when she was health minister, 
she is not willing to continue with a sacrifice she considers 
disproportionate. [passage omitted] 

