<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Sweden </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Request for More Troops for Bosnia Denied </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302173294 Stockholm Radio Sweden in English 1715 GMT 23 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2302173294 </F>
<F P=104>  Stockholm Radio Sweden </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sweden has turned down a United Nations request to 
send more troops to Bosnia on the grounds that it presently has 
no soldiers trained to carry out the assignment. Sixteen other 
countries, including Norway, have also been approached. And, 11 
Swedes are receiving intensive training in Serbo-Croatian in 
order to serve as interpreters in the Nordic UN battalion in 
Bosnia. They are to replace Swedish interpreters of Yugoslavian 
origin who, it is feared, run the risk of being considered 
biased by Bosnia's ethnic groups on the grounds of their accents 
or family names. 

</TEXT>

