<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Work Begins for Delivering `Essentials' to FYROM </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2302182994 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1615 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2302182994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara (A.A) -- Foreign Ministry Deputy Spokesman 
Ferhat Ataman has announced that work is under way regarding the 
delivery of urgent essentials to Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav 
Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM]. 
  Ataman stated that the Greek Government's 16 February 
decision imposing an economic embargo on Macedonia exacerbated 
the already dire economic conditions in that country. 
  Ataman said that work is under way to supply Macedonia with 
petrol and fuel oil at convenient prices adding Turkey will open 
its ports to transportation destined for Macedonia. 
  It is expected, Ataman further stated, that the Macedonian 
Deputy Prime Minister Jovan Andonov will visit Ankara. 

</TEXT>

