<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Asked To Clarify Kurdish Meeting in Moscow </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2302202694 London Kanal-6 Television in Turkish 1700 GMT 
23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2302202694 </F>
<F P=104>  London Kanal-6 Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Kurdish conference being organized in Moscow is 
causing a crisis in the ties between Turkey and Russia. Turkey 
is not satisfied with Russia's explanations on the issue and is 
asking for additional clarification. 
  Russian Ambassador to Turkey Albert Chernyshev indicated 
that 
he has little information on the conference in which 
organizations affiliated with the PKK [Workers Party of 
Kurdistan] are participating and added that Russia has not 
changed its views on Turkey's unity and territorial integrity. 
  In a statement to a Russian paper, President Suleyman 
Demirel 
said Russia has shown sensitivity toward Turkey's difficulties 
as regards terrorism. But, Demirel added, our people are 
extremely sensitive. He stated the need for additional 
explanations so that the people don't get the impression that 
Russia is supporting terrorism. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

