</HEADER>

<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   General Assembly Adopts Human Rights Bill </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2402104994 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1005 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2402104994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Feb.24 (A.A) -- The General Assembly of 
parliament adopted a bill which approves protocol No.4 which 
foresees additional human rights, on Wednesday [23 February]. 
  Under the protocol which has been adopted, no person will be 
expelled or banned from entering to the country which he is a 
citizen. In addition, the protocol bans the mass expulsion of 
foreigners from the country. 
  The protocol ensures that everyone who is living legally in 
a 
country is entitled to circulate, choose his residence, or leave 
the country, freely. 
  These rights can not be restricted unless they threaten 
national unity, public order, and the freedoms and rights of 
others. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-39975 </DOCNO>
