<H3> <TI>   Demirel, Izetbegovic Discuss Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2302183094 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2302183094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over still of President Suleyman </F>
Demirel] 
  [Text] It has been reported that Bosnia-Herzegovina has 
submitted a request to the United Nations asking that Turkish 
and Pakistani troops be sent to the country. President Suleyman 
Demirel spoke with Bosnia-Herzegovina President Alija 
Izetbegovic today by telephone. 
  According to a statement issued by the Press Center of the 
President's Office, Izetbegovic said that his country submitted 
a request to the United Nations asking that Turkish and 
Pakistani troops be sent to his country. Izetbegovic also 
requested the participation of Turkey in all meetings concerning 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and thanked Demirel for Turkey's contribution 
to the recent developments. Izetbegovic also briefed Demirel on 
the situation in Sarajevo and other regions. 

</TEXT>

