<H3> <TI>   UNHRC To Visit, Assess Conditions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2502092094 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2502092094 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The National Human Rights Commission has assured the 
international community that it will further strengthen and 
propagate the culture of human rights in the country and 
function with maximum transparency. Addressing the UN Human 
Rights Commission in Geneva, one of its members, Mr. Justice 
Virendra Dayal, said that the Commission is enjoying statutory 
autonomy and its functions cover all violations of human rights 
mentioned in the Vienna Document. He told the delegates and the 
nongovernment organizations that the Commission will make 
extensive visits to various states beginning with Jammu and 
Kashmir, Punjab, Assam, and other northeastern states to assess 
the human rights condition. Mr. Dayal said the Commission is in 
touch with the armed forces and police in matters relating to 
protection and promotion of human rights and training of their 
personnel. 

