<F P=100> UNITED KINGDOM </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hogg, Croatia's Granic Discuss Bosnia Solution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402184894 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1800 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2402184894 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Mate Granic, Croatian deputy prime minister and 
foreign minister held talks with Douglas Hogg, minister of state 
for foreign relations at the Foreign Office. They discussed a 
peaceful solution for Bosnia-Herzegovina. The talks were held 
in the light of the Croat-Muslim cease-fire agreement, which 
aroused great interest in the British media. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

